  "steps": [
    {
      "id": "l3-articles-theory",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Three words for \"the\"",
      "body": "# der, die, das\n\nEvery German noun has a **gender**: masculine, feminine, or neuter. The word for *the* changes with the gender:\n\n| Article | Gender | Example | English |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **der** | masculine | der Mann | the man |\n| **die** | feminine | die Frau | the woman |\n| **das** | neuter | das Kind | the child |\n\nThe gender is not always logical (*das Mädchen* — the girl — is neuter!), so **learn each noun together with its article**. Nouns are always written with a **capital letter** in German."
    },
    {
      "id": "l3-ex-match-articles",
      "type": "exercise",
      "title": "Match noun and meaning",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l3-ex-match-articles",
        "type": "matching",
        "prompt": "Match each German noun with its English meaning.",
        "card_ids": ["de-der-mann", "de-die-frau", "de-das-kind", "de-der-hund"],
        "pairs": [
          {"left": "der Mann", "right": "the man"},
          {"left": "die Frau", "right": "the woman"},
          {"left": "das Kind", "right": "the child"},
          {"left": "der Hund", "right": "the dog"}
        ],
        "direction": "target_to_source"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "l3-ex-free-article-cat",
      "type": "exercise",
      "title": "Choose the article",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l3-ex-free-article-cat",
        "type": "free_text",
        "prompt": "Write the correct article + noun for \"the cat\".",
        "card_ids": ["de-die-katze"],
        "accept": ["die Katze", "Die Katze"],
        "distractors": ["der Katze", "das Katze"],
        "hint": "*Katze* is feminine.",
        "direction": "source_to_target"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "l3-ex-free-article-house",
      "type": "exercise",
      "title": "Choose the article",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l3-ex-free-article-house",
        "type": "free_text",
        "prompt": "Write the correct article + noun for \"the house\".",
        "card_ids": ["de-das-haus"],
        "accept": ["das Haus", "Das Haus"],
        "distractors": ["der Haus", "die Haus"],
        "hint": "*Haus* is neuter.",
        "direction": "source_to_target"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "l3-sein-theory",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "The verb \"sein\" (to be)",
      "body": "# sein — to be\n\n**sein** is the most important German verb, and it is irregular. Memorise the full pattern:\n\n| German | English |\n|---|---|\n| **ich bin** | I am |\n| **du bist** | you are *(informal)* |\n| **er / sie / es ist** | he / she / it is |\n| **wir sind** | we are |\n| **ihr seid** | you are *(plural)* |\n| **sie / Sie sind** | they are / you are *(formal)* |\n\nExample: **Ich bin müde.** — *I am tired.*"
    },
    {
      "id": "l3-ex-match-sein",
      "type": "exercise",
      "title": "Match the forms of sein",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l3-ex-match-sein",
        "type": "matching",
        "prompt": "Match each form of \"sein\" with its English meaning.",
        "card_ids": ["de-ich-bin", "de-du-bist", "de-er-ist", "de-wir-sind", "de-sie-sind"],
        "pairs": [
          {"left": "ich bin", "right": "I am"},
          {"left": "du bist", "right": "you are"},
          {"left": "er ist", "right": "he is"},
          {"left": "wir sind", "right": "we are"},
          {"left": "sie sind", "right": "they are"}
        ],
        "direction": "target_to_source"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "l3-ex-cloze-iam",
      "type": "exercise",
      "title": "Complete with sein",
      "exercise": {
